       <div class="content"> 
        <div id="slide1" class="slide"> 
         <img src="/about/images/region/big1.jpg" alt="Snow capped Mount Baldy over UCR." width="464" height="232"> 
         <p class="credit">Photo Credit: Larry McGrath</p> 
         <h3>San Gabriel Mountains Overlooking the UCR Campus</h3> 
         <p>UCR's Humanities and Social Sciences Building framed by snow-capped San Gabriel Mountains. Just a short drive from the UCR campus, mountain resort locations such as Big Bear Lake, Mt. Baldy Village, and Lake Arrowhead offer hiking, skiing, snowboarding, camping, boating, fishing, horseback riding and other recreational activities.</p> 
        </div> 
        <div id="slide2" class="slide"> 
         <img src="/about/images/region/big2.jpg" alt="Mission Inn. " width="464" height="232"> 
         <h3>Mission Inn</h3> 
         <p>From its modest beginnings as a 12-room adobe boarding house to its current stature consisting of 239 guest rooms, the National Historic Landmark Mission Inn Hotel &amp; Spa has been the keystone of downtown Riverside since 1876.</p> 
        </div> 
        <div id="slide3" class="slide"> 
         <img src="/about/images/region/big3.jpg" alt="The Alhambra Court at the Mission Inn. " width="464" height="232"> 
         <h3>The Alhambra Court at the Mission Inn</h3> 
         <p>The fourth floor of the Mission Inn features the Moorish-themed Alhambra Court, built in 1923-1924. The suite includes a huge fireplace and beams of Mexican cedar. The Carmel Tower overlooks the corner of Sixth and Orange Streets in Riverside</p> 
        </div> 
        <div id="slide4" class="slide"> 
         <img src="/about/images/region/big4.jpg" alt="Riverside's Chinese Memorial Pavilion. " width="464" height="232"> 
         <h3>The Chinese Memorial Pavilion</h3> 
         <p>The Pavilion is a memorial to the early Chinese pioneers, including those from Jiangmen, Riverside's sister city and the home of the Chinese citrus industry, who contributed to the development of agriculture transportation and commerce in Riverside and Southern California. Funded by the Republic of China (Taiwan), the City of Riverside and the non-profit Chinese Pavilion Committee, it is located on the grounds of the Riverside Public Library.</p> 
        </div> 
        <div id="slide5" class="slide"> 
         <img src="/about/images/region/big5.jpg" alt="View of the Cityscape. " width="464" height="232"> 
         <h3>Unique Spanish and Mediterranean Architecture</h3> 
         <p>The influence of the Spanish and Mediterranean architectures are seen throughout the city, including a significant portion of downtown.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <a class="previous" title="Previous" onclick="my_glider.previous();return false;" href="#">Previous</a> 
